      "last_updated": "2026-04-28",
      "status": "current",
      "_note_2026_04_28b": "Amendment 2 to ADR 011 fixed three harness gaps surfaced by the first 14B grid: (1) reference scenarios were duplicated per Ollama model — split scenarios in run_grid so reference runs once per grid; (2) models not pulled in Ollama errored 5× per scenario — added _probe_pulled_models(base_url) hitting GET /api/tags once at run start, absent models record a single skip_reason cell instead; (3) no per-cell sample response text in baseline JSON, forcing curl-based investigation of wrong-shape outputs — aggregate() now captures first non-errored response_text truncated to 500 chars into a new sample_response_text field. Schema additions are additive (skip_reason: Optional[str], sample_response_text: str), schema_version stays at 1. Floor test updated to allow skipped cells. Three new unit tests cover the fixes.",
      "_note_2026_04_28": "ADR 011 latency benchmark harness — sibling to ADR 010's conversation eval. Captures TTFT / decode_tps / total_ms per (model, scenario, seed) cell on the actual ICP hardware (single-machine first: Apple M5 Pro 24 GB). Five v1 scenarios (warm-short, prefill-4k, prefill-16k, decode-throughput, chat-realistic-shallow) + one Anthropic reference shot for the explicit competitor benchmark. Streaming Ollama HTTP /api/chat client captures TTFT from first content delta and decode_tps from done-event eval_count/eval_duration (model-self-reported, excludes HTTP overhead). Bootstrap-CI gate on paired-cell metric diffs (LOWER_IS_BETTER for TTFT/total_ms, HIGHER_IS_BETTER for decode_tps), same statistical floor as conversations/gate.py. CLI run_bench.py supports --scope nightly|pr; PR mode is the floor-gate subset (~5-10 min) for fast checks, nightly is the full grid (~45-90 min on M5 Pro 24 GB) for canonical baseline capture. Stable-key JSON output committed to baselines/, anchored by machine_info (model_label, ram_gb, ollama_version, knob_stack); diffs across baselines surface which knob produced which effect. Opt-in floor test JARVIS_LATENCY_BENCH=1 mirrors test_baseline_floor.py discipline; skips silently until baseline-0 is captured. 28 unit tests covering scenario shape determinism, streaming-timing logic with stubbed httpx, percentile aggregation, machine-info capture, and bootstrap-CI verdict logic across all four cases (improvement/regression/equivalent/insufficient_data). No production-path changes — pure dev infra. Substrate landed in this chunk; baseline-0 capture + knob-loop chunks (flash_attention, kv_cache_q8, prefix_caching verify, speculative decoding) follow per ADR 011 migration path."
    },
