      "_note_2026_04_28": "Catalog correctness pass: fixed Qwen3 native contexts (32K not 40K/256K), Devstral native (256K not 384K), renamed Gemma 4 27B (nonexistent) to Gemma 4 26B-A4B; added Qwen3-14B, Qwen3-30B-A3B-Instruct-2507, Qwen3-4B-Instruct-2507, Granite 4.0 H-Micro/H-Tiny/H-Small. All entries with unverified Ollama tags carry internal=True (filtered from user picker until tags are verified against ollama.com/library) — user-pickable list is the 6 original entries with verified tags. Each internal entry carries a TODO: verify Ollama tag comment. Tool_mode taxonomy renamed: native→native_qwen3, json_fallback→adapted, limited→excluded_from_tools. Added probe_runtime_load() + GET /api/local/runtime/load — pure-Python (psutil + Ollama /api/ps), macOS branch graduates to Tauri-native after ADR 003. Catalog gained `bytes_per_kv_token` + `attention_arch` (transformer|mamba|swa, Literal-typed); `effective_footprint_bytes(entry, ctx_len)` is the helper that feeds the future memory-pressure auto-downgrade (the actual user problem: free RAM drops, model + KV cache no longer fits, swap to a smaller one rather than OOM). Rolled back this same chunk: InferenceRouter skeleton, ProfilePack 9-vertical taxonomy, slot_class field, KEEP_ALIVE_BY_SLOT policy table, route audit on every done event. Reason: the per-request classifier and multi-slot dispatch were over-engineered for the actual problem (single chat model + memory-pressure downgrade); the load-bearing pieces (catalog correctness, runtime probe, footprint helper, atomic config IO, licensing) survive. ADRs 004/005 amended with the rollback note. Cross-link added to latency-benchmark (ADR 011) — sibling harness captures TTFT / decode_tps / total_ms baselines per (model, scenario) on the actual ICP hardware (M5 Pro 24 GB first), gates future optimization knobs (flash_attention, kv_cache_q8, prefix caching, speculative decoding) under a bootstrap CI. local-models.md gained a 'Latency baseline' subsection."
